ce:section.ce:para:
To further study the catalytic properties, the steady-state kinetics of Pd150-PCRP NPs of TMB and H2O2 was determined. The initial velocity of the catalytic oxidation reaction was calculated. The concentration of H2O2 or TMB was used as a variable parameter while other parameters remained unchanged. As illustrated in 
                        Fig. 5(a, b), two typical Michaelis-Menten curves with two substrates for TMB and H2O2 were obtained. The maximum initial velocity (V

                           max
                        ) and the Michaelis–Menten constant (K

                           m
                        ) were calculated through the Lineweaver–Burk equation.
